TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$showHint =3;

$y = random(23,27,1);
$x = random(17,22,1);
$A1 = sqrt(($x)**2+($y)**2);
$A2 = atan($x/$y)*180/pi;


BEGIN_TEXT
<strong>If you don't solve this problem correctly in $showHint tries, you can get a hint.</strong>
$PAR
Solve the following problem using analytical techniques: Suppose you walk \($y.0\,\textrm{m}\) straight north and then \($x.0\,\textrm{m}\) straight west.
$PAR

a) How far are you from your starting point?
$PAR

\{ans_rule(40)\} \(\textrm{m}\)

$PAR
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("$A1"));

BEGIN_TEXT
b) What is the compass direction of a line connecting your starting point to your final position?

$PAR

\{ans_rule(40)\} \(\textrm{degrees West of North}\)

$PAR
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("$A2"));

